      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "I would only say that something like this might be beyond the scope of a node on the network. Bitcoin Core is designed specifically to 1) validate transactions and blocks and 2) connect and share information over the P2P network. All of this is supposed to happen at the minimal cost to the hardware it is running on. That said, it looks like there are some interfaces already out there for monitoring fee distributions like you mentioned, and I'm not sure how important of a value add it is to all users that they have this feature.  ",
